# Repo charter

This is `motive4artists.org` — the website of MOtiVE 4 Artists Inc. (NY 501(c)(3) pending). Read `AGENTS.md` for the full charter before any non-trivial change.

Non-negotiables:

- No README.md. Comments and `docs/adr/` carry the docs. Comments explain *why*, never *what*.
- Server-first Next.js (App Router). Server Actions for mutations, not API routes.
- Zod validation on every Server Action input and every webhook payload.
- Conventional Commits, enforced by the commit-msg hook.
- Compliance footer (`components/compliance/`) appears on every page.

When you are about to write a `README.md`, stop. Put the intent into a code comment at the call site, or into `docs/adr/NNNN-<slug>.md` if it's an architectural decision.

When you are about to write a comment that narrates what the code does (`// increment counter`, `// loop through items`), stop. Either delete it or rewrite it to explain *intent* or *trade-off*.
